postcontent:
USED AND MODIFIED --- Austria made ISSC M22 hand gun.  Good condition.  It is about the same size as a Glock model 19.  Excellent training hand gun for inexpensive 22 lr ammo.  I will meet you at Interlake Sporting Association (Redmond/Kirkland area) if you wish to inspect and shoot before purchasing.
 I originally purchased this pistol as a cheap training gun in place of my XD9.   With that in mind, I had a local gunsmith make the following four improvements:
 1) Grip bumps filed off.  The stock finger grooves were badly placed and fell under the fingers rather than between the fingers.
 2) Trigger covered.  The stock trigger does not feel like a XD or Glock.   The stock trigger is razor sharp and cuts your finger.  This was remedied by covering the trigger with two layers of heat shrink tubing.  Now, the trigger is awesome, but, the trigger safety is disabled.
 3) White dot sites painted black.  The front site repainted Day Glo, Hi Viz Orange.
  4) Right hand take down flange lowered.  The take down bump interferes with drawing from a holster.  This was lowered to facilitate smooth draws.
 Before inquiring about this firearm, please review the listing photos and compare this pistol to a stock gun.  THIS IS NOT A STOCK GUN.  Personally, I really enjoyed the modifications and thought they were big improvements over a stock pistol.
 The ISSC M2 shoots best with CCI Mini Mags, but will do okay with cheap Federal bulk pack ammo as long as the slide rails are well lubed.  FFL transfer only.  Buyer pays FFL fees, and shipping fees, if any.
